# Diary — <work item name>

> Spec: [`spec.md`](./spec.md) • Progress: [`progress.md`](./progress.md)
> Started: <YYYY-MM-DD>

Chronological narrative of this work item: discoveries, decisions, plan changes, surprises, dead
ends, and resolutions. Append-only — new entries go at the **top** (newest first). Old entries are
not deleted or rewritten; if you're wrong about something, write a new entry correcting it.

**Always write a diary entry when**:

- A decision in `decisions.md` changes (supersession).
- A phase or iteration shape changes (scope, files touched, acceptance).
- An assumption from `context.md` turns out to be wrong.
- A blocker is hit, and again when it's resolved.
- A review surfaces a finding that affects the plan (not just the code).
- A discovery during coding shifts the spec.

Each entry is short — one paragraph, plain language. Pretend you're writing to a teammate who'll
read this in three months and needs to understand "what happened on this work item."

